Sigma.js is a nopen-source lightweight JavaScript library to draw graphs, using the HTML canvas element.

You could find it on www.sigmajs.org


The goal of this project is to bind sigma.js in opa. 


=== HOW TO USE ===

make all 

will call in this order :
make clean
make opp
  => Will create the js-binding
make plugin
  => Will create the opa package with opafunction to call the js binding
make demo
  => Will compile the opa demo code
make run
  => Will launch the demo
  
Then goto http://localhost:8080 and enjoy.

With opa ubuntu package.
== COMPILE WITH ==
Opa compiler (c) MLstate -- version 0.9.2 -- build 1591 (DB3 => MONGODB)
Opa compiler (c) MLstate -- version 0.9.1 -- build 1555
Opa compiler (c) MLstate -- version 0.9.1 -- build 1518


== DON'T COMPILE WITH ==
